law.text:
Without limitation of any right or defense of an insurer, the following acts by or on behalf of an insurer are not considered to be a waiver of a provision of a policy or of a defense of the insurer under the policy:
acknowledging the receipt of notice of loss or claim under the policy;
furnishing a form for:
reporting a loss or claim;
giving information relating to a loss or claim; or
making proof of a loss;
receiving or acknowledging receipt of a form or proof listed in item (2) of this section, completed or uncompleted;
investigating a loss or claim under a policy; or
engaging in negotiations toward settlement of a loss or claim.
